# 9. Why This Works

Every new bit depends only on the previous bit.

If

```
previous=1

new=1
```

then adjacent count increases.

Otherwise,

count remains unchanged.

Thus,

keeping

```
position

pairs

previous bit
```

is sufficient.

Dynamic Programming avoids recalculating identical states.

