# 13. Common Mistakes

❌ Counting every `1` instead of adjacent `"11"` pairs.

---

❌ Forgetting to increase the pair count only when

```
previous = 1

current = 1
```

---

❌ Not taking modulo after additions.

---

❌ Using recursion for `n = 1000` without considering Python's recursion depth.

---

❌ Returning only `dp[k][1]` instead of

```
dp[k][0] + dp[k][1]
```

because valid strings may end in either `0` or `1`.

